and say I was Burt.

919
00:36:14,439 --> 00:36:15,939
(screams)

920
00:36:15,940 --> 00:36:17,440
If that's not our killer
then where is he?

921
00:36:23,482 --> 00:36:26,416
I believe you have something
that belongs to me.

922
00:36:26,418 --> 00:36:28,718
(chuckles)

923
00:36:28,720 --> 00:36:31,154
Burt, I presume.

924
00:36:35,594 --> 00:36:37,861
(Jim groaning)

925
00:36:37,863 --> 00:36:39,196
Can I keep him?

926
00:36:39,198 --> 00:36:40,463
JIM:
Get her off me!

927
00:36:40,465 --> 00:36:41,331
She's insane!

928
00:36:41,333 --> 00:36:42,599
Well, you better start talking.

929
00:36:42,601 --> 00:36:44,100
Where's the man
that paid you?

930
00:36:44,102 --> 00:36:47,504
I don't know. He saw some tall
guy with dark hair in a suit.

931
00:36:47,506 --> 00:36:48,605
He took off.

932
00:36:48,607 --> 00:36:49,873
That's Lucifer.

933
00:36:49,875 --> 00:36:51,308
Yeah.

934
00:36:51,310 --> 00:36:54,177
Recognized you
from the beach party.

935
00:36:54,179 --> 00:36:55,545
Of course.
Tommy Bahama.

936
00:36:55,547 --> 00:36:56,913
It's good that you found me,

937
00:36:56,915 --> 00:36:58,748
'cause I've been meaning
to ask you something since then.

938
00:36:59,785 --> 00:37:01,051
Where'd you get the water slide?

939
00:37:01,053 --> 00:37:02,219
I'd love one for Lux.

940
00:37:02,221 --> 00:37:03,620
I'm not sure where I'd put it...

941
00:37:03,622 --> 00:37:04,621
I want my package.

942
00:37:04,623 --> 00:37:07,624
Now.

943
00:37:07,625 --> 00:37:10,626
I should've known Jana left it
with you after I saw her at Lux.

944
00:37:10,629 --> 00:37:13,430
That's why she was only there
a few minutes-- to stash it.

945
00:37:13,432 --> 00:37:16,366
No, the reason that she left
so quickly was because

946
00:37:16,368 --> 00:37:19,035
she was unhappy
that I didn't have sex with her.

947
00:37:19,037 --> 00:37:21,037
Yeah, I don't believe you.

948
00:37:21,039 --> 00:37:22,806
No one says no
to a girl like that.

949
00:37:22,808 --> 00:37:25,976
I'm finding it hard to believe
myself, trust me, but, uh,

950
00:37:25,978 --> 00:37:29,145
as for your package, Burt...

951
00:37:29,147 --> 00:37:30,780
I don't have it.

952
00:37:30,782 --> 00:37:32,182
Liar.

953
00:37:32,184 --> 00:37:33,883
Oh, come now.

954
00:37:33,885 --> 00:37:35,285
Surely a little bit of cocaine

955
00:37:35,287 --> 00:37:37,387
isn't worth all
the senseless killing.

956
00:37:37,389 --> 00:37:39,356
Cocaine?

957
00:37:39,358 --> 00:37:42,092
What's in that package
is far more valuable than drugs.

958
00:37:42,094 --> 00:37:43,893
Oh.
It's my ass on the line,

959
00:37:43,895 --> 00:37:45,462
and that stupid bitch Jana...

960
00:37:50,936 --> 00:37:53,336
You don't speak of her that way.

961
00:37:53,338 --> 00:37:56,206
You promised Jana the world

962
00:37:56,208 --> 00:37:59,009
and everything
she could ever desire.

963
00:37:59,011 --> 00:38:02,112
Money, drugs,
a life of pleasure,

964
00:38:02,114 --> 00:38:05,782
but she deserved
better than that...

965
00:38:05,784 --> 00:38:08,718
better than you...

966
00:38:08,720 --> 00:38:10,787
or me.

967
00:38:10,789 --> 00:38:15,692
I mean, what did either of us
really give her?

968
00:38:15,694 --> 00:38:17,227
Empty pleasure?

969
00:38:18,063 --> 00:38:20,096
Hey, man...

970
00:38:20,098 --> 00:38:21,798
we can work something out.

971
00:38:21,800 --> 00:38:23,466
(chuckles)

972
00:38:23,468 --> 00:38:25,602
I'll find the package.
I'll get paid. We'll...

973
00:38:25,604 --> 00:38:27,504
We're similar in a lot of ways,
aren't we, Burt?

974
00:38:28,340 --> 00:38:30,674
Except for one.

975
00:38:30,676 --> 00:38:34,844
You're a bad man and I'm not.

976
00:38:36,982 --> 00:38:39,082
I'm much...

977
00:38:39,084 --> 00:38:41,851
much worse than that.

978
00:38:42,854 --> 00:38:44,120
(shouting)

979
00:38:48,226 --> 00:38:50,427
(shouts)
Lucifer!

980
00:38:53,098 --> 00:38:54,664
There's your killer,
detectives.

981
00:38:54,666 --> 00:38:56,733
Think you'll find he feels
quite remorseful

982
00:38:56,735 --> 00:38:58,385
about the life he's led.

983
00:38:58,386 --> 00:39:00,036
Please... okay, p-please,
just-just arrest me, okay?

984
00:39:00,038 --> 00:39:01,137
Okay, get up.
I'm sorry.

985
00:39:01,139 --> 00:39:02,806
I'm sorry, I'm sorry.
Stand up.

986
00:39:02,808 --> 00:39:04,808
I'm sorry.

987
00:39:08,747 --> 00:39:10,547
Hey.

988
00:39:10,549 --> 00:39:12,182
About what you heard
in the van...

989
00:39:12,184 --> 00:39:13,550
Hey, it doesn't matter...

990
00:39:13,552 --> 00:39:15,685
except something
still bothers me.

991
00:39:15,687 --> 00:39:19,723
Burt went to a lot of trouble
for a single drug deal.

992
00:39:19,725 --> 00:39:24,394
Yeah, well... the guy had
a reputation to protect.

993
00:39:24,396 --> 00:39:27,297
You know? One person
steals from him,

994
00:39:27,299 --> 00:39:29,099
everyone else thinks
they can, too.

995
00:39:29,101 --> 00:39:32,435
CHLOE:<i> All right.</i>
<i> But then who has the package?</i>

996
00:39:37,042 --> 00:39:40,343
How... how did you find me?

997
00:39:40,345 --> 00:39:42,912
I'm sorry I took it.
I was desperate.

998
00:39:42,914 --> 00:39:44,347
I'm broke.

999
00:39:44,349 --> 00:39:46,082
When the stewardess let it slip

1000
00:39:46,084 --> 00:39:48,485
how much cash she was gonna make
from this delivery, I...

1001
00:39:48,487 --> 00:39:50,754
I thought it was drugs.

1002
00:39:50,756 --> 00:39:53,189
I was gonna sell them.

1003
00:39:53,191 --> 00:39:54,924
Then I opened it.

1004
00:39:54,926 --> 00:39:57,127
One of them broke.

1005
00:39:57,129 --> 00:39:59,929
I spilled a little on myself.
Now...

1006
00:40:01,466 --> 00:40:04,801
What the hell
is happening to me?

1007
00:40:04,803 --> 00:40:07,036
(grunts)

1008
00:40:07,038 --> 00:40:08,671
(choking)

1009
00:40:27,993 --> 00:40:31,528
Hey, I've been looking
for you everywhere.

1010
00:40:31,530 --> 00:40:33,329
I tracked your phone's GPS.

1011
00:40:33,331 --> 00:40:36,599
Well... here I am.

1012
00:40:37,903 --> 00:40:40,470
Well, we should wrap up
the arrest report,

1013
00:40:40,472 --> 00:40:43,673
and by that I mean paperwork,
not some celebratory drink

1014
00:40:43,675 --> 00:40:46,176
that you'll then
turn into a moment.

1015
00:40:46,178 --> 00:40:48,645
(chuckles)
Yes, well...

1016
00:40:48,647 --> 00:40:50,647
I've changed my mind
about that, actually.

1017
00:40:50,649 --> 00:40:53,383
I realized it would never
work out between us.

1018
00:40:53,385 --> 00:40:54,684
Really?
Yes.

1019
00:40:54,686 --> 00:41:00,089
So, from now on,
no more attempts at moments.

1020
00:41:00,091 --> 00:41:04,327
I'd be honored to, uh, simply
continue working by your side...

1021
00:41:05,163 --> 00:41:07,363
...if you'll have me.

1022
00:41:07,365 --> 00:41:08,498
Of course.

1023
00:41:08,500 --> 00:41:09,933
Good.
Yeah.

1024
00:41:09,935 --> 00:41:11,668
It's not like you
to give up, but...

1025
00:41:11,670 --> 00:41:13,303
Oh, no, I haven't given up.

1026
00:41:13,305 --> 00:41:16,406
I had a...
an epiphany, of sorts.

1027
00:41:16,408 --> 00:41:19,709
You deserve someone worthy
of you and that isn't me.

1028
00:41:19,711 --> 00:41:21,744
That's not what
I've been saying, Lucifer.

1029
00:41:21,746 --> 00:41:24,614
I know.
It's what I'm saying.

1030
00:41:24,616 --> 00:41:28,251
You... deserve someone better

1031
00:41:28,253 --> 00:41:30,253
because you, Detective,

1032
00:41:30,255 --> 00:41:33,022
are selfless
to a nauseating degree.

1033
00:41:35,527 --> 00:41:37,527
You always put
your daughter first,

1034
00:41:37,529 --> 00:41:39,329
even though the ungrateful
urchin does nothing

1035
00:41:39,331 --> 00:41:40,730
to contribute to the rent.

1036
00:41:40,732 --> 00:41:42,432
(laughs)
So...

1037
00:41:42,434 --> 00:41:44,868
you deserve someone
worthy of that grace.

1038
00:41:44,870 --> 00:41:48,004
Someone who knows that every
crime scene breaks your heart,

1039
00:41:48,006 --> 00:41:50,406
even though
you'd never admit it.

1040
00:41:50,408 --> 00:41:52,675
Someone who
actually appreciates

